Data Lake is a big container to store data in it's native format.

There is no limit of amount of data that can be stored. It can store structured, semi-structured and streaming data.

It helps BA analyze the data immediately without having to process the data.

Data Lake vs Hadoop: Hadoop is just one technology that can be used as part of Data Lake architecture. 

Why Data Lake Gen 2?
Combined the features of data lake gen 1 + Blob storage (Providing multiple tiers)

Difference between Data Lake Gen 2 and Blob Storage:
Provides hierarchical namespace. 
Enables big data analytics.
Compitable with Hadoop.
Supports multiple Azure Integrations.


